To create a static responsive website with four items in columns, you can use HTML and CSS. I'll provide you with a basic example of how to structure the HTML and how to style it using CSS to achieve a four-column layout that is responsive. This code will result in a webpage that displays four columns on larger screens, and the columns will stack on top of each other on smaller screens, such as mobile devices.

Here's a simple example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
