  </div>
  <div class="column" style="background-color:#ccc;">
    <h2>Column 3</h2>
    <p>Some text..</p>
  </div>
  <div class="column" style="background-color:#ddd;">
    <h2>Column 4</h2>
    <p>Some text..</p>
  </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
```

In the HTML code above:
- Each `.column` represents an individual column.
- The `.row` class is used to contain the columns. The `::after` pseudo-element with `clear: both;` is used to clear the float, ensuring that following elements are displayed correctly.
