2. **Create a Provider Component:**
   Create a provider component that will wrap your application or the part of it where you want the popup to be available. This provider will use the `useState` hook to manage the visibility of the popup and any other state it needs to track.

   ```javascript
   // AlertProvider.js
   import React, { useState } from 'react';
   import AlertContext from './AlertContext';

   const AlertProvider = ({ children }) => {
     const [alert, setAlert] = useState({ open: false, content: null });

     const showAlert = (content) => {
